Citations
Date: 15/12/1983
Source: NZ Journal of Agriculture
Author:
Vol / Page: 46
Edition:
Quote: Split - When one of a dog trial trio takes a fit of the 'hermits' and goes off on its own. Split is also used to describe the successful division of a sextet into two trios.
